A "particle" is that thingy that moves around in the billiard. It always moves with velocity measure 1, by convention.  Currently there are two types of particles:   Particle , which propagates as a straight line.  MagneticParticle , which propagates as a circle instead of a line (similar to electrons in a perpendicular magnetic field).   There are two ways to create a particle. The first one is to provide the constructor with some initial conditions:  x0   =   rand ();   y0   =   rand ();  φ0   =   2 π * rand ()   # an angle is enough  p   =   Particle ( x0 ,   y0 ,   φ0 )   Particle{Float64}
position: [0.324647, 0.142048]
velocity: [0.573107, 0.81948]  To create a  MagneticParticle  simply provide the constructor with one more number, the angular velocity:  ω   =   0.5  mp   =   MagneticParticle ( x0 ,   y0 ,   φ0 ,   ω )   MagneticParticle{Float64}
